Here are various tests for the point and polygon classes...

To run the automatic unit tests, you need to have node.js installed as well as
the node module nodeunit. The easiest way to install nodeunit is to use the
node package manager 'npm'. Just type
  npm install nodeunit
in the tests/ directory. To run the unit tests, call
  ./run
  
For a visualization of how bezier curves of svg polygons are interpolated by
straight line segments, open visual-path-test.html in a browser.
